<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id8f686b70-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s2211c"><num value="2211c">§ 2211c.</num><heading> Poverty measurement methods</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Administrator of the Agency, in consultation with financial intermediaries and other appropriate organizations, should have in place at least 1 method for implementing partners to use to assess poverty levels of their current incoming or prospective clients.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id8f686b71-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">(<ref href="/us/pl/87/195">Pub. L. 87–195</ref>, pt. I, § 254, as added <ref href="/us/pl/108/484/s3">Pub. L. 108–484, § 3</ref>, <date date="2004-12-23">Dec. 23, 2004</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/118/3926">118 Stat. 3926</ref>; amended <ref href="/us/pl/115/428/s4/d">Pub. L. 115–428, § 4(d)</ref>, <date date="2019-01-09">Jan. 9, 2019</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/132/5514">132 Stat. 5514</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id8f686b72-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id8f686b73-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id8f686b74-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2019—<ref href="/us/pl/115/428">Pub. L. 115–428</ref> amended section generally. Prior to amendment, section related to development of poverty measurement methods and application of methods.</p>
</note>
